I like the colors! It&#39;s helpful.

On another note, I see that you&#39;re thinking about new names for the
letters, and some of these are quite good. One thing that I don&#39;t like
about the revised names is that they include several male names, but
no female names. It would be nice to rectify that... perhaps &#39;Moira&#39;
for #22!

One problem with the English names for letters in the Roman alphabet
is that many of them rhyme, so we end up on the phone saying &quot;B as in
Bravo, D as in Delta&quot;, or whatever. When considering new letter names,
I think it&#39;s good to come up with names that are easily recognized
over a noisy connection.

Ted


